	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-1840299879" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hey Nick!</p><p>This kind of thing isn't supported, so you'll have to handle it manually (i.e. query for one object, read the "fk" column, use it to query the other db), which has the advantage of at least being very understandable. You can also get fancy if you want - like this: <a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fstackoverflow.com%2Fquestions%2F13648974%2Fsymfony2-doctrine2-cross-database-join-column-throws-mapping-exception%3AtrXcatuRE9WE_8_qTO9w-1m5KDU&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">http://stackoverflow.com/quest...</a>. This approach can even be used to "join" between a relational db and a nosql db. But measure whether it's worth your trouble first :).</p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
	                </li>
